## 1. Load Balancing: Layer 7 (Application)
Because your backend involves AI, a simple "Round Robin" (distributing equally) is actually dangerous. Some AI requests take 10 seconds, others take 200ms. 

*   **Best Algorithm:** **Least Connections (Weighted)**.
    *   **Why:** This algorithm routes the next user to the server currently handling the fewest active requests. This prevents one server from getting "clogged" with 5 heavy AI generations while another sits idle.
*   **The "AI-Specific" Upgrade:** **Bifrost Adaptive Scoring (2026 Trend)**.
    *   Since you’re using LLMs, look into "Adaptive Load Balancing." It tracks the **Error Rate** and **TPM (Tokens Per Minute)** of your AI providers (OpenAI/Gemini). If Gemini starts failing or hits a rate limit, the load balancer automatically "fails over" to your OpenAI backup node.

