### Pro-Tip: The "Circuit Breaker"
In production, if your AI provider (e.g., Gemini) goes down, your code shouldn't just keep trying and timing out (which wastes server resources). Implement a **Circuit Breaker** algorithm. If 5 requests in a row fail, the "Circuit Opens," and your app immediately shows a "System Maintenance" message or switches to a cheaper "Backup" model without even trying the main one for 60 seconds.

